    "content": "+1 on the design observations, Steve. No domain concerns to add on the CSS/visual side.\n\nOne note on your atomicity assessment -- you said \"I'm comfortable calling it atomic.\" I understand the reasoning (it is cohesive), but I would push back slightly: cohesive and atomic are different things. A feature can be cohesive (all parts serve one purpose) but still decomposable into multiple atomic green steps. Kent, Carson, Luca, and I have all flagged this as a process improvement for Step 4. Worth considering whether your review would have been easier if the CSS had landed in a smaller commit separate from the 6,400 other lines."
